reviewText:
I have seen her performances on TV while in the Philippines. She has a movie that is a first for her and it's in English. She has been compared to Celine Dion. Well what I've heard puts her in a class by herself. And if I'm not mistaken she writes a lot of her own material something that Celine Dion doesn't do.

The people in this country are missing out big time because they take the Filipino for granted. One only has to look to groups like Journey who have a Filipino as their lead singer.
